    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<h2>Marshal Rennic Thale — Loftwick Militia Commander</h2>\n<p><em>Late forties. Twenty-two years militia. Married, two grown sons. Honest, competent, careful with his orders. Council-instructed to be aware of the party's movements during the Closure review period. Will not act without orders. Will not refuse an order he has been given. May be persuadable to support the courier-chain investigation.</em></p>\n<h3>Combat behavior</h3>\n<p><strong>Subdues rather than kills.</strong> If his whistle-response is invoked at the Vesten Quill encounter, three militia (including Thale himself) arrive within three minutes; they take prisoners back to the city barracks.</p>\n<h3>Statblock summary (CR 4, PB +2)</h3>\n<p>AC 18 (chain mail + shield) · HP 65 (10d8+20) · Speed 30 ft. · Init +1 · Passive Perception 13</p>\n<p>STR 16 · DEX 13 · CON 14 · INT 12 · WIS 13 · CHA 14. Saves: STR +5, CON +4. Skills: Athletics +5, Intimidation +4.</p>\n<h3>Actions</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Multiattack.</strong> Two attacks: longsword + shield bash, or two longsword.</li>\n<li><strong>Longsword.</strong> +5 melee, 1d8+3 slashing (1d10+3 two-handed).</li>\n<li><strong>Shield Bash.</strong> +5 melee, 1d4+3 bludgeoning, target DC 13 STR save or knocked prone.</li>\n<li><strong>Heavy Crossbow.</strong> +3 ranged, range 100/400, 1d10+1 piercing.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Reactions</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Parry.</strong> When hit by a melee attack he can see, +3 to AC against that attack.</li>\n<li><strong>Subdue (1/short rest).</strong> May knock an enemy reduced to 0 HP unconscious instead of killing them.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Source</h3>\n<p><em>Blooming Rot, Part 2 — Phase 5.</em> See <em>Phase 5 — Loftwick NPCs → Marshal Rennic Thale</em> for the three conditions he requires before helping.</p>",
        "public": ""
      },
